I'm trying to use ProFontWindows.ttf, if that helps.</description><pubDate>Fri, 23 Aug 2013 00:38:57 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2415/set-ttf-font-for-window-titles/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by mschaefer for &lt;p&gt;Is it possible to select a (downloaded and installed) ttf font for the window titles?
I'm trying to use ProFontWindows.ttf, if that helps.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2415/set-ttf-font-for-window-titles/?answer=2416#post-id-2416</link><description>You should start with installing the font to your system (depends on the disto I guess). Once that is done use the following as font line in your i3 config:
&lt;pre&gt;font pango: ProFontWindows 10&lt;/pre&gt;
10 is the font size, change it as you wish. You possibly need to install &lt;code&gt;libpango&lt;/code&gt; library to make this work. Cf. [user guide](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#fonts) for some additional information.</description><pubDate>Fri, 23 Aug 2013 09:02:30 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2415/set-ttf-font-for-window-titles/?answer=2416#post-id-2416</guid></item></channel></rss>